<DOC><DOCNO> AP880609-0168 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-09-88 1808EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p AM-KittyDukakis     06-09 0236</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Kitty Dukakis,230</SECOND><HEAD>Mrs. Dukakis Heads Home From Hospital</HEAD><DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Kitty Dukakis, the wife of likely Democraticpresidential nominee Michael Dukakis, went home from the hospitalThursday to further recover from delicate spinal surgery.   Her husband made sure the ride home was comfortable, positioninga pillow behind his wife's neck as they drove away fromMassachusetts General Hospital in Boston toward their home insuburban Brookline.   She made several jokes about her inability to turn her headbecause of a neck brace she must wear for several weeks.   ``The one promise that my doctors have made is that the nightMichael accepts the nomination I can take this collar off,'' Mrs.Dukakis said. That will come at the Democratic National Conventionin mid-July.   Asked when she would resume campaigning for her husband, Mrs.Dukakis smiled and said:   ``The doctors and nurses are right here and my husband is to myright so I have to tell you that I promised them that I will notget back on the campaign trail until the convention.''   Mrs. Dukakis, 51, began experiencing pain and numbness severalweeks ago, and a preliminary diagnosis indicated two herniateddiscs in her neck. She underwent surgery six days ago.   Two bone fragments were taken from Mrs. Dukakis' hip and fusedto the ruptured discs. Because of that procedure, Mrs. Dukakis isexpected to walk with a limp for several weeks.</TEXT></DOC>